<br>
Burning Meadow<br>
<br>
Come lady lie beneath these swaying leaves;<br>
Beckoning golden rye, beside mountain streams;<br>
Just you and I, so won’t you come;<br>
The lovers gentle sigh, arms entwined as one;<br>
Come lady lie, together let us dream;<br>
Dare not to be shy, embrace what love may bring;<br>
Our spirits soar to the sky, through wispy clouds we run;<br>
Over the fields we fly, dreaming of love yet unsung;<br>
Come lady lie, enter romantic scene;<br>
Gently side by side, passion smolders, steams;<br>
Kisses softly lit, fires eternal as the sun;<br>
Dusk enters night, lovers absorbed in fun;<br>
O come lady lie, in these arms of peace;<br>
Dream into my eyes your lips I tenderly kiss;<br>
Lovers lying thigh to thigh, so won’t you come;<br>
Swaying perfect time, rhythm lovers drum;<br>
Come my Queen and lie, make known your need;<br>
These gentle hands mine, desire to set you free;<br>
Fingers trace love lines, slowly softly strum;<br>
So won’t you come, come my Queen and lie;<br>
With me in this burning meadow of love.<br>
