<br>
Love’s Promise Broken<br>
<br>
In meadows gleaming golden, ‘neath blue sky<br>
Where larks aflutter dance upon the breeze<br>
Did once love also dance ‘twixt you and I<br>
A love we thought enduring as the trees.<br>
<br>
A kiss, a touch, the warmth of soft embrace<br>
And whispered promises of love divine<br>
That time had not the power to displace<br>
Now soured as the most acidic wine.<br>
<br>
The words that sang, now bitter curses hiss<br>
Caressing fingers point accusingly<br>
Lips curl in anger where they once did kiss<br>
And coldness lives where once the heart was free.<br>
<br>
The lovers once in bliss, in anger part<br>
Despair, in victory, claims the broken heart.<br>
<br>
