<br>
Appearing from the void of nothingness,<br>
I stood upon a ridge watching her…an image of myself<br>
The winds caressed her face, winds of the west, warm and tender<br>
Her emerald eyes gazed across fields of flowers that danced before her.<br>
Her cloak moving slightly against the breeze, as if tugging for her to move on.<br>
She turned her face upward to the sky filled with light of the moon.<br>
The gypsy king she desired and whispered for each morning was nowhere near,<br>
Like a sinking tide, she knelt upon the ground…the sword gleaming in her hands.<br>
“I am a warrior, I live by a code…why must they take from me, when I do not take from them”<br>
Her words were soft yet strong while laced with pain and sorrow.<br>
<br>
A single tear slid silently down her face and fell upon the blade,<br>
It moved along the edge, splitting it apart…blood dripping upon the ground<br>
Traveling to the blade’s end, the sword pointed itself toward the furthest star.<br>
A flash of lightning exploded upon the night, darkness distrubed at midnight.<br>
The globe of mist swirled around the woman, never looking up as she raised her fist<br>
Her hand opened revealing the wound her heart felt as the lightning slammed against it.<br>
As quickly as it started, it ended and darkness prevailed again…<br>
The warrior who knew only death and suffering rose slowly as if defying good and evil<br>
“My heart just won’t let go and this sleeping tiger must remain asleep.  Do not awaken me.”<br>
