Helplessly observing as the scene unfolded before him.<br>
His piercing blue eyes gazed in wonder as he saw the woman approach the opposite ridge.<br>
Long cold and remote his heart lept, could this be her, the princess he had given his love so long ago.<br>
Breathing deeply his heart burst into flames of a long sleeping desire.<br>
The breeze bore the familiar smell of the woman he loved.<br>
Watching her kneel for what seemed an eternity he saw her rise and draw her glimmering sword.<br>
Plunging recklessly from the ridge upon which he stood he sprinted across the meadow separating them, even as electricity filled the air.<br>
Screaming her name he watched as the fiery bolt slammed into her outstretched hand.<br>
She turned and their eyes locked momentarily.  <br>
In the sea of emerald and pain he saw the soft love she held for him yet.<br>
And she was gone.<br>
<br>
Kneeling in the spot she stood he raised his clichéd fist heavenward.<br>
A long painful roar burst from his cracked lips, echoing across the valley the sound of sorrow mixed with rage.<br>
A tear slid from his cheek and fell as he lowered his head to the ground.<br>
The warm wetness of her blood and his tear mixed together staining his cheek.<br>
Empty and still he notices a scroll in his clenched hand.<br>
