My Dearly Beloved,<br>
<br>
The night is the most scariest for me, once sleep used to be welcomed and now I fear it.  I roam the meadows in the evenings while most nestle happily upon their pillow.  How many years has it been since the cloak of darkness allowed me the glory of a peaceful sleep?  It has been so long that I cannot even remember when that was.  But tonight's deprivation of sleep is the greatest of all, for I have looked inside of myself and these things I know.<br>
<br>
I died within.  I watched myself devoured piece by piece, the life sucked out. To think that you have suffered daily for years kills me worse than the death that myself met.  There is no way that I can look you in the eyes without feeling shame for what you endured.  My enemies have destroyed what I had left in me, any hope that I cherished to seek freedom from them has been removed with the swiftness of a sword.<br>
<br>
I know now, that returning to the life I embraced is out of the question.  To the Gods, I am Lady of Pain and to you, a betrayer.  To myself, I am a failure.  My mind no longer sees the freedom that my heart desires, I am a slave to my sword and until the Gods bestow upon me the release of this clutch, I am just an object.  Forgive me....<br>
 <br>
With deepest affection,<br>
Lady of Pain <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jazzerbojangles>JazzerBojangles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#000000>(6/23/03 8:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Burning Meadow</span><hr size=1> Pondering the scroll the Gypsy King sat in the evenings growing shadows.  Disbelief was replaced slowly with the dawning of a new resolve.  Standing suddenly he summoned his faithfull steed, mounted and rode briskly to the North.  The ever present laughter just beneath the survace was non existant in the scroll, could it be so grim.<br>
