<br>
Standing before her in his true form, black tendrils slithering from his form, grasping at the gray mist and leaving their marks upon it.  He shifts into what could be considered as a crouch if there were a ground, his huge black wings stretched out behind him.<br>
<br>
&quot;I see you received my summons.&quot;  The smile upon his face twisted by the enormous fanged teeth formally hidden beneath his black lips.  The smile disappears, his wings flare up, and a hungry gleam flashes across his features.  &quot;I hunt for you...&quot; <br>
<br>
The stench of the hunt fills the room, blowing in through the hole until the spawn closes it and the fear chokes her awake.<br>
<br>
*********************************************************<br>
<br>
Sitting up quickly eyes wide and filled with alarm as the sweat mats against her hair that clings tightly to her face.  Knuckles white from clutching the sheets as the nightmare swallowed her deep into its core, she moves to leave the vision trap quickly tossing back the covers and running for the fresh cool air just outside the front door.<br>
<br>
Sliding down along the wall, sinking to the ground she tries to remember how she got here when she was from somewhere else.  How does she make the past understand they are not what she wants or needs, how does she make the present understand how much she wants and needs him?  Where is he when she needs him to calm the beast that lurks in the darkness?<br>
<br>
The late night townspeople stare at her oddly as they hurry back to a destination only they know of.  Do they see the beast she carries inside in her or do they know she is really a lie and just a slave who escaped her master?  The weary warrior weakly stands up allowing the wall to aid her like a worn old woman in need of assistance to even move.  Tomorrow she will seek him out....tomorrow she will find the one she loves and he will bring the life back to her.<br>
<br>
Tomorrow she finds Jesse....<br>
