_______________________________________________________________<br>
<br>
“And so there I was standing on this lizard’s tail practicing my portal gate spell.”  The little halfing was saying while looking up at the wizard, a tall slender elf, who was watching the docks intently.  “When this paladin charged at me, waving her sword and shield around like there was no tomorrow! Hmpf!  Had it been my way that noble no good for nothing dinner plate wearer would not have seen tomorrow!”  Her hands placed firmly on her hips while fire flickered in her eyes telling the story to Rizmorik.<br>
<br>
The wizard calmly looked down at the rambling druid wondering to himself how did he manage to get so drunk from one of his concoctions that he ported himself into Pulbrook and woke up to find her leaning over peering at him oddly.  He swears she was talking the moment his mind cleared of the drunken festivity and hasn’t stopped chatting since.  In time, he found her company to be enjoyable and refreshing from the solitude life that wizards tend to follow. When it came time for him to depart he offered to show her new places if she cared to travel with him, she accepted eagerly and so it began.  His life has not been dull since that day, let alone quiet.  “Pray tell, little one, why would the good knight be coming at you that way?”  He asked while moving his attention back to the man strutting toward a ship, his anger rising to why such scum is allowed to share the ground that he does.<br>
<br>
“First, that scrawny silver piece announced she was Zumie, Noble Knight of Jilanli Temple, like I care!  Then she proceeds to inform me…mind you, her words…”inform me” that tail gating is not allowed.  Can you imagine such nerve!”  Rizmorik raised one hand to his temple and began to rub it slowly, his mind searching for answers to where in the master wizardry training did halfings come into play.  “Pity she just didn’t understand what you were doing.” He replied kindly though thinking next time he should leave her at home with Sative while he traveled doing research work.<br>
<br>
Upon seeing the slave master board his ship, Rizmorik gazed across to the inn where the woman once stood outside, he felt her presence but more so felt her desperation.   Feeling helpless and at a loss against the forces greater than he possessed he could only channel portions of the Lady of Pain through him hoping to ease her suffering.<br>
<br>
It was time to return home, he was drained and needed rest to regain his powers that seemed to be seeping away by an unknown force.  Palming his hand upward to the sun, the tiny crystal sparkled briefly before exploding into colors surrounding the pair, enveloping them then vanishing into thin air.<br>
